wikipedia_page.main: John Spencer Ritchie "Jock" Duncan  (26 July 1921 – 12 September 2006) was the last member of the Sudan Political Service to leave at independence in 1956. He then became a diplomat and was British Consul General in Muscat, High Commissioner to Zambia, Ambassador to Morocco, and High Commissioner in the Bahamas.

response: * 26 July – John S. R. Duncan, diplomat (died 2006)
* John S. R. Duncan (1921–2006), British administrator in Sudan, then diplomat, high commissioner and ambassador
